    "narrative": "The **Zurich Zebras** lineup for April 11 is anchored by the dual-threat prowess of **Yordan Alvarez** (71.69) and **Trea Turner** (70.89). While **Yordan Alvarez** faces a stern test against Luis Castillo, his elite xwOBA remains the cornerstone of our offensive ceiling. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** benefits significantly from the combination of a favorable matchup against Pfaadt and high-efficiency stolen base conditions, as Pfaadt\u2019s delivery speed profile creates a prime environment for **Trea Turner** to swipe bags. **Kyle Schwarber** (65.10) also remains an essential play in that same matchup, as his elite power metrics keep him locked in the lineup despite the inherent volatility of his profile.\n\nStrategic platoon advantages are driving our middle-infield production today. **Colt Keith** (64.95) and **Hyeseong Kim** (61.56) are high-confidence starts due to favorable matchups against Junk and Jack Leiter, respectively. **Hyeseong Kim**, in particular, benefits from wind-out conditions and an opponent with a slow delivery to the plate, which bolsters his stolen base projection despite the uncertainty of a pending lineup. On the defensive side, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (63.05) is a vital inclusion; his matchup against Braxton Ashcraft provides a massive +14% platoon boost that easily secures his place in the outfield, keeping him well above the bench threshold.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the optimizer was the exclusion of **Josh Smith** (43.49), who sat just above the Zebras' 40.0 floor but failed to displace the high-scoring floor of **Jerar Encarnacion** (52.34). While **Josh Smith** benefits from favorable wind and platoon splits, his projected bottom-of-the-order slot significantly dampens his run-production potential. We remain cautious regarding **Christian Yelich** (40.14), who barely clings to a starting spot; his matchup against Foster Griffin is concerning due to a severe SP skill disadvantage (-19%) and a harsh platoon penalty, making him the most likely candidate to be swapped if official lineups confirm a disadvantageous order slot later today.",
